sentences.english: I killed dozens of eels every day to meet the demand.
sentences.chinese: 每天为了满足需求，我都要杀几十条鳝鱼。

sentences.english: The taste of eel is delicious.
Some looked like little eels, most have paired teeth at the head end.
sentences.chinese: 有的看上去像小鳝鱼，大多数的头部有着成对的牙齿。

sentences.english: Dai Dapan had been drowned by thousands of eels which held him under water until he died.
sentences.chinese: 戴大盘被几千条鳝鱼拖在水里直至淹死。

sentences.english: This paper is to establish a highly sensitive method for determination of residues diethylstilbestrol in Monopterus albus by high performance liquid chromatography.
sentences.chinese: 建立鳝鱼中己烯雌酚残留量的高效液相色谱测定方法。

sentences.english: Then they took thousands of eels from the pond and released them in the river.
sentences.chinese: 他们把放生池里数千条鳝鱼放到江里。

sentences.english: Japanese person doesn't necessarily like eel.
sentences.chinese: 日本人未必就一定喜欢吃鳝鱼。

sentences.english: Tide was the main hydrology course, which influenced the Shanyutan Phragmites australis marsh of Min River estuary.
sentences.chinese: 潮汐是影响闽江河口鳝鱼滩芦苇湿地的主要水文过程。

sentences.english: Eglish people do not like eating eels.
Wei also liked to dig out eels, catch frogs, and trap turtles.
sentences.chinese: 魏也喜欢掘出鳝鱼，捕捉青蛙，诱捕乌龟。

sentences.english: Methane Emission in Reed Marsh of Minjiang River Estuary and the Discussing of Environmental Influencing Factors;
sentences.chinese: 潮汐是影响闽江河口鳝鱼滩芦苇湿地的主要水文过程。

sentences.english: The eel wriggled out of my fingers.
sentences.chinese: 那条鳝鱼从我的指缝间滑走了。
